<ul><li> A rarely seen function of the iKnow in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebComic/CommanderKitty" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebComic/CommanderKitty">Commander Kitty</a></em>, <a class="urllink" href="http://www.commanderkitty.com/2009/08/23/obedience/">as Zenith demonstrates on Fortiscue when he questions her plans.<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>
</li><li> In <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/HiToTsukiToHoshiNoTama" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/HiToTsukiToHoshiNoTama">Hi to Tsuki to Hoshi no Tama</a></em>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RidiculouslyCuteCritter" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RidiculouslyCuteCritter">paget</a> slaves often have magical shock collars.
<div class="indent"> <strong>Bid</strong>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EloquentInMyNativeTongue" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/EloquentInMyNativeTongue">For collar off... anything I to do.</a>
