<h2 class="bold font-l">Ratchet: Deadlocked</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
The Deadlock Collars are designed to keep the DreadZone contestants &quot;cooperative.&quot; They can electrically torture the wearers and could even kill them. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="gbmz8h" data-video-descrip="Ren's put one on you, and he's not afraid to activate it! (Footage by Lionel Orlando on YouTube)" data-video-title="Boyfriend to Death 2" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/gbmz8h_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/gbmz8h.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ShockCollar" data-video-tropename="Shock Collar" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Visualnovel/Boyfriendtodeath" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/gbmz8h.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Boyfriend to De...</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="fyna6y" data-video-descrip="After Megabyte &amp;quot;repairs&amp;quot; Hexadecimal, he administers a shock collar to keep her under his control." data-video-title="ReBoot" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/fyna6y_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/fyna6y.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/ShockCollar" data-video-tropename="Shock Collar" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="WesternAnimation/ReBoot" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/fyna6y.jpg">
